<leg xml:space="preserve" billnum="HB0483" sponsor="Doug Owens" designation="HB" otherSponsor="Heidi Balderree" otherHouse="Senate" sess="2026GS" fileno="2026FL1431" date="2/4/2026 09:02:373" printDate="02-23 10:18" subVer="0" minVer="0" office="LEGISLATIVE GENERAL COUNSEL" actionDate="" impact="code"><info><nextbuid>4</nextbuid><aminfo anum="0" effdate="05/06/2026"><seclist><sect action="E" src="code" buid="1" uid="C11-46c-S101_2026050620260506" sort="11 46c01010020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">11-46c-101</sect><sect action="E" src="code" buid="2" uid="C11-46c-S102_2026050620260506" sort="11 46c01020020260506" mtype="section" effdate="05/06/2026">11-46c-102</sect><sect src="uncod" untype="effdate" buid="3" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" mtype="uncod" effdate="05/06/2026"/></seclist></aminfo></info><tbox><sinfo><nextpairid>0</nextpairid></sinfo><st numlevel="1" lineno="1" slineno="0-1">Flower Sales Modifications</st><sessionhead>2026 GENERAL SESSION</sessionhead><statehead>STATE OF UTAH</statehead><sponsorhead>Chief Sponsor: Doug Owens</sponsorhead><otherSponsorhead>Senate Sponsor: Heidi Balderree</otherSponsorhead></tbox><lt numlevel="1" lineno="2" slineno="0-2"><lthead lineno="3">LONG TITLE</lthead><gdhead lineno="4">General Description:</gdhead><gd numlevel="1" lineno="5" slineno="0-5">This bill addresses local regulation of cut flower sales.</gd><hphead lineno="6">Highlighted Provisions:</hphead><hp numlevel="1" lineno="7" slineno="0-7">This bill:<hl numlevel="1" lineno="8" slineno="0-8" level="1">defines terms;</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="9" slineno="0-9" level="1">establishes that a political subdivision may not prohibit the sale, trade, or transfer of cut <ln numlevel="1" lineno="10" slineno="0-10"/>flowers if the person selling, trading, or transferring the cut flowers is permitted to grow <ln numlevel="1" lineno="11" slineno="0-11"/>flowers on the person's private property; and</hl><hl numlevel="1" lineno="12" slineno="0-12" level="1">clarifies that a political subdivision may require a person selling, trading, or transferring <ln numlevel="1" lineno="13" slineno="0-13"/>cut flowers to obtain a business license.</hl></hp><moni numlevel="1" lineno="14" slineno="0-14" display="none">Money Appropriated in this Bill:</moni><moniNone lineno="15">None</moniNone><oc numlevel="1" lineno="16" slineno="0-16">Other Special Clauses:</oc><ocNone lineno="17">None</ocNone><sa numlevel="1" lineno="18" slineno="0-18">Utah Code Sections Affected:<saent numlevel="1" lineno="19" slineno="0-19"><snhead>ENACTS:</snhead><sn num="11-46c-101" src="code" uid="C11-46c-S101_2026050620260506" buid="1" sort="11 46c01010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="20" slineno="0-20"><bold>11-46c-101</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn><sn num="11-46c-102" src="code" uid="C11-46c-S102_2026050620260506" buid="2" sort="11 46c01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="21" slineno="0-21"><bold>11-46c-102</bold>, Utah Code Annotated 1953</sn></saent></sa></lt><enacthead lineno="22"/><enact numlevel="1" lineno="23" slineno="0-23">Be it enacted by the Legislature of the state of Utah:</enact><bdy><bsec buid="1" num="11-46c-101" type="enact" src="code" uid="C11-46c-S101_2026050620260506" sort="11 46c01010020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="24" slineno="1-1" sn="1"><section numlevel="1" lineno="26" slineno="1-3" number="11-46c-101" type="enact"><secline lineno="24">Section 1. Section <bold>11-46c-101</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><headchap number="11-46c" numlevel="1" lineno="25" slineno="1-2">46c. Regulation of Cut Flower Sales</headchap><catline lineno="26"><bold>11-46c-101<parens/>. Definitions.</bold></catline><sectionText lineno="27"><para/><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="24" groupid="19" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">As used in this chapter:</amend></sectionText><subsection ssid="1-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="28" slineno="1-5" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1000" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="7" groupid="6" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Cut flower" means a flower or flower bud that has been removed from the flower's or <ln numlevel="1" lineno="29" slineno="1-6"/>flower bud's parent plant.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="30" slineno="1-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1001" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="13" groupid="10" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">"Political subdivision" means:</amend><subsection ssid="1-3" dnum="_-o:a-i" numlevel="1" lineno="31" slineno="1-8" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1002" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(a)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="18" groupid="14" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">a municipality as that term is defined in Section <xref depth="3" refnumber="10-1-104">10-1-104</xref>; or</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="1-4" dnum="_-o:b-i" numlevel="1" lineno="32" slineno="1-9" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="2"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1003" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(b)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="23" groupid="18" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">a county.</amend></subsection></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="2" num="11-46c-102" type="enact" src="code" uid="C11-46c-S102_2026050620260506" sort="11 46c01020020260506" numlevel="1" lineno="33" slineno="2-1" sn="2"><section numlevel="1" lineno="34" slineno="2-2" number="11-46c-102" type="enact"><secline lineno="33">Section 2. Section <bold>11-46c-102</bold> is enacted to read:</secline><catline lineno="34"><bold>11-46c-102<parens/>. Actions allowed regarding cut flowers.</bold></catline><subsection ssid="2-1" dnum="_-o:1-i" numlevel="1" lineno="35" slineno="2-3" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1" placement="noreturn"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1004" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(1)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="7" groupid="5" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">Subject to Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="11-46c-102(2)">(2)</xref>, if an ordinance, resolution, or policy of a political subdivision <ln numlevel="1" lineno="36" slineno="2-4"/>permits a person to grow flowers on the person's private property within the political <ln numlevel="1" lineno="37" slineno="2-5"/>subdivision's boundaries, the political subdivision shall permit the person to trade, sell, <ln numlevel="1" lineno="38" slineno="2-6"/>or otherwise transfer cut flowers from the flowers grown on the person's private property.</amend></subsection><subsection ssid="2-2" dnum="_-o:2-i" numlevel="1" lineno="39" slineno="2-7" ea="amend" anum="0" owner="jchristopherson" style="1" level="1"><display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1005" style="1" owner="i" level="1" amendtag="start">(2)</amend></display><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="12" groupid="9" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="end">A political subdivision may require a business license for a person described in <ln numlevel="1" lineno="40" slineno="2-8"/>Subsection <xref depth="4" refnumber="11-46c-102(1)">(1)</xref> to trade, sell, or otherwise transfer cut flowers, except that the political <ln numlevel="1" lineno="41" slineno="2-9"/>subdivision may not deny the issuance of a business license on the basis that the person <ln numlevel="1" lineno="42" slineno="2-10"/>grows flowers or is trading, selling, or transferring cut flowers.</amend></subsection></section></bsec><bsec buid="3" type="uncod" untype="effdate" src="uncod" uid="EF0000" sort="UZEFF" langlock="true" numlevel="1" lineno="43" slineno="3-1" sn="3"><section type="uncod" untype="effdate" display="false" src="uncod"><secline lineno="43">Section 3.  <bold>Effective Date.</bold></secline><sectionText lineno="44"><amend anum="0" ea="amend" pairid="1" groupid="1" style="1" owner="jchristopherson" level="1" amendtag="both">This bill takes effect on <effdate uid="code" date="5/6/2026">May 6, 2026</effdate>.</amend></sectionText></section></bsec></bdy><foot><rev><tm>2-4-26 9:26 AM</tm></rev></foot></leg>